title: Ween - [1990] God Ween Satan_ The Oneness
description:
From: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GodWeenSatan:_The_Oneness

GodWeenSatan: The Oneness was the first official Ween album, released on Twin/Tone Records in 1990. Their first album introduces several key themes for the group, including their eclecticism, gonzo sense of humor, and their demon god/mascot The Boognish.

This album would later be reissued in 2001 by Restless Records in a special \"25th Anniversary Edition\" (the album had been only 11 years old), featuring digitally remastered sound, new packaging, and the inclusion of three bonus tracks integrated into the original album\&#039;s playlist.

The album contains tracks that are still staples of Ween\&#039;s live performances, such as \"You Fucked Up,\" \"Fat Lenny,\" \"Marble Tulip Juicy Tree,\" and \"L.M.L.Y.P.\"
